      <hedline>
        <hl1>A Compassionate Man</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Lucy Schenck letter lauds Elvis Mitchell's July 30 article on filmmaker Wim Wenders (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Many thanks to Elvis Mitchell for his understanding and sympathetic description of Wim Wenders's genius and lack of American commercial success. When I first saw ''Wings of Desire'' on video years ago, I had finally stumbled on a brilliant filmmaker who did not need to demonstrate a genius that was devoid of compassion and sensitivity for subjects that were often lone, abandoned, forgotten and, worst of all, unpopular. No wonder Mr. Wenders isn't distributed with commercial ease in this country.</p>
        <p>LUCY SCHNECK  Cranford, N.J.</p>
      </block>
